# Build artifacts — .tex sources and references.bib are the canonical
# source of truth. Each paper subdirectory has its own build/ directory
# that is fully derived (xelatex/biber output) and should never be
# committed.
#
# Note: paper/phantom_codes.pdf, paper/phantom_codes_supplementary.pdf,
# and paper/pubmedbert_finetuning.pdf are intentionally *not* gitignored
# — they're the manually-promoted snapshots (via `make snapshot-*`) that
# give casual readers a one-click preview without needing a local LaTeX
# install.
build/
phantom_codes/build/
pubmedbert/build/

# Editor cruft that sometimes appears alongside LaTeX
*.synctex.gz
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk

# biblatex/biber intermediates
*.bcf
*.run.xml
